{"lemma":"تُهَمِ","slug":"تُهَمِ","root":"ت.ه.م","root_slug":"ت-ه-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ه-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4151","n4153","n4154"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8F%D9%87%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"impeachment, charge, accusation (both the act and its content)","examples":[{"text":"تَوْجِيهُ ٱلتُّهْمَةِ","english":"directing the charge"},{"text":"ثُبُوتُ ٱلتُّهْمَةِ","english":"establishing the charge"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tuh.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4151","headword_ar":"تَهِمَ","root":"thm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahamN","text_ar":"تَهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahaAmapN","text_ar":"تَهَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(flesh-meat, JK, Msb, K, and milk, Msb, and oil, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became altered for the worse, and stank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * Msb, K: *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(flesh-meat, TK)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had a foul odour; it stank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the heat)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, vehement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense, with stillness of the wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-  Also, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahamN","text_ar":"تَهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was penetrated by the heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was smitten by the hot wind, and in consequence became lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And, (JK, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahamN","text_ar":"تَهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ate much of the pasture"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotakovara mina AlmaroEaY","text_ar":"اِسْتَكْثَرَ مِنَ المَرْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it was not wholesome:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disapproved the pasture"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotanokara AlmaroEaY","text_ar":"اِسْتَنْكَرَ المَرْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and did not find it wholesome,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and his condition became bad."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And, said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His impotence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inability, became apparent, and he became confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, and unable to see his right course."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n4153","headword_ar":"تَهَمٌ","root":"thm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahom","text_ar":"تَهْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land descending"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN mutaSaw~ibapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ مُتَصَوِّبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK, here and afterwards, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaSaw~iyap","text_ar":"مُتَصَوِّيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the sea;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahamapN","text_ar":"تَهَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) mentioned by IKt, from Ez-Ziyádee, from As: (TA:) these two words seem to be [originally] inf. ns. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tihaAmapu","text_ar":"تِهَامَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [and accord. to F,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ahomapu","text_ar":"التَّهْمَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tihaAmapu","text_ar":"تِهَامَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [but J says,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ahamapu","text_ar":"التَّهَمَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the place of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tihaAmapu","text_ar":"تِهَامَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though it were [originally] the inf. n. un., accord. to the saying of As that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ahamu","text_ar":"التَّهَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the medial radical, is an inf. n. from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tihaAmapu","text_ar":"تِهَامَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) for the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahaAy^im","text_ar":"تَهَايِم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tihaAmapu","text_ar":"تِهَامَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and thus meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parts of Tihámeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to the JK, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lands descending to the sea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] do descend to the sea: (K, TA:) so says As: (TA:) and [hence] the rájiz says, (namely, Sheytán Ibn-Mudlij, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"naZarotu waAlEayonu mubiynapu Alt~ahamo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I looked, the eye distinguishing Et-Taham"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, and Ham p. 659,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Et-Tihámeh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ibid.) ―         -b2-  [As inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahima","text_ar":"تَهِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ahamu","text_ar":"التَّهَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehemence of heat, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stillness of the wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And hence Tihámeh is said to be thus called. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n4154","headword_ar":"تَهِمٌ","root":"thm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to flesh-me.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Altered for the worse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a foul odour; stinking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN tahimapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ تَهِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land vehemently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely, hot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Riyáshee, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sleeping;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahinN","text_ar":"تَهِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lEv","text_ar":"لعث"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}